Around 100 religious leaders from various churches in Cape Town have taken to the streets today to protest against revised Level 3 regulations. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana has the story. #DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Around 100 religious leaders from various churches in Cape Town took to the streets on Friday to protest revised Level 3 regulations. READ: Sebokeng religious leaders say churches shouldn't be closed President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that church gatherings may go ahead but with a maximum of 50 people indoors. Churches want 50 percent capacity for their churches and also to be declared essential workers. Trying to handover a memorandum to Parliament, pastors and police came face to face. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana has the full story in the video above.